Line and stacked column chart - Infection weeks 16

In this step we are going to build a line and stacked column chart in our report that shows infection week over week since the start of the pandemic.

That being said, the goal is to create a report  that shows infection rate for the last 12 weeks from the maximum date of selection. To do so we need to create a calculated columns to show a dynamic x-axis that change via date slicer.

Calculated Columns

Week Start Date = 'Calendar'[Date] - WEEKDAY('Calendar'[Date],2)+1
Week End Date = 'Calendar'[Date] - WEEKDAY('Calendar'[Date],2)+6
Week Duration = FORMAT('Calendar'[Week Start Date],"M/D")& "-"  &FORMAT ('Calendar'[Week  End Date],"M/D")
Last 12 weeks = 
VAR _a = Max('Calendar'[Week End Date]) -120
Var _b = Max('Calendar'[Week])+120
RETURN
IF(And('Calendar'[Week End Date] >= _a ,'Calendar'[Week]<=_b ),"Last Twelve Weeks", "Other Weeks")

N.B. We have to sort week duration in x-axis by week end date.



Steps for this report

1. Drag and drop line and stacked column chart from visualizations.

2. Drag and drop

  • Week duration column from calendar table to shared axis in fields box
  • Last 12 weeks from calendar table to shared axis in fields box
  • Infection Rate from measure table to column values in fields box
  • Infection WOW% from measure table to line values in fields box
  • Total infection from measure table to tooltips in fields box
  • Total cases from measure table to tooltips in fields box

3. Legend - on

  • Color - White, 20% darker
  • Font family - Arial
  • Text size - 10pt
  • Style - Line and markers

4. X-axis - on

  • Color - White, 20% darker
  • Text size - 9pt
  • Font family - Arial
  • Title - off

5. Y-axis - on

  • Color - White, 20% darker
  • Text size - 9pt
  • Font family - Arial
  • Display units - None
  • Title - off
  • Stroke width - 1
  • Line style - Dotted
  • Show secondary - on
  • Aline zeros - on
  • Y-Axis line :

                           - Color - #f79a7e, theme color 8, 40% lighter

                                      -  Text size - 9pt

                           - Title - off

6. Data colors 

  • Infection WOW% color -  #f47853, theme color 8, 20% lighter
  • Default color - White, 10% darker 

7. Data label - on

  • Color - White, 10% darker
  • Display units - None
  • Text size - 9pt
  • Font family - Arial
  • Customize series - on

                                               - Color -  White, 10% darker                                        - Color - #f79a7e, theme color 8, 40% lighter
